The paper focuses on the development and evaluation of autonomous driving systems, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of machine learning techniques such as imitation learning and reinforcement learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation of the approaches using metrics provided by the simulation platform indicates that the paper may also be relevant to the computer vision (cs.CV) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the use of end-to-end models trained via machine learning suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
